    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Element&nbsp;</strong>water;&nbsp;<strong>Type&nbsp;</strong>utility (Sp);&nbsp;<strong>Level&nbsp;</strong>1;&nbsp;<strong>Burn&nbsp;</strong>0</p>\n<p>You can create water as the cantrip @Compendium[pf1.spells.snj78r5rw96btfjn]{Create Water}, purify water as if using @Compendium[pf1.spells.xi1uouy7qlpfaqlr]{Purify Food and Drink}, and dry wet creatures and objects as if using @Compendium[pf1.spells.a6isom7wx0nmhwfp]{Prestidigitation}. While you cannot lift water into the air using this ability, you can create mild currents in a body of water by concentrating. These currents are strong enough to run a water mill as if the mill were being turned manually by a creature with a Strength score equal to your Constitution score.</p>"
